eas:</span><ul start=1><li><strong>Strategic Approach</strong><span> - How the organization approaches its marketplace.</span><li><strong>Relationships</strong><span> - How the organization manages its internal and external relationships.</span><li><strong>Daily Operations Philosophy</strong><span> - How the organization manages its daily work.</span><li><strong>People Philosophy</strong><span> - How the organization develops its people.</span></ul><p><span>Each of the main areas has a series of scales which explore different aspects of how the organization operates. Since some aspects of a company’s culture are more important to you than others, we suggest you think about the or aspects of a company’s culture are most important to you. Are there a few aspects that are "must haves"? Are there any aspects that are potential "deal breakers"? What is it about the "must haves" that energize and motivate you? What is it about the "deal breakers" that demotivate you?</span><p><span>Finally, think about what could be done to put more of what you like into a job as well as how the position might be modified to lessen the aspects you might not like. These thoughts could be the basis for an exploratory discussion with a hiring manager, a current supervisor, or a coach. Included in your report below, in the right-hand column, are some questions to consider while preparing for these career discussions.</span><p><span>Remember, the goal is not to find the perfect position. While that would be great, more goal is to make it as aligned with your personal preferences as possible. That way, you will be as productive and satisfied as possible, which is a win-win for you and the organization.</span><p><span>Thanks again for taking Strategia Analytics Diagnostics™ <b>My Preferred Organization™</b> diagnostic.</span><p><span>With Appreciation,<br>The Strategia Analytics Team</span><p><br><br><h3>Main Area I: Strategic Approach</h3><table border=1 cellpadding=10 style=width:70%><tr style