earch and science, Strategia Analytics Diagnostics™ <strong>Candidate Cultural Alignment Profile™</strong> reveals your preferences specific to the work environment and organizational culture that will allow you to do your best work. The <strong>Candidate Cultural Alignment Profile™</strong> is a decision-support tool designed to help you make a more informed choice when considering a career transition.<p>The report below shows your responses to 54 questions which are organized into 4 main areas:<ul><li><strong>Strategic Approach</strong> - How the organization approaches its marketplace.<li><strong>Relationships</strong> - How the organization manages its internal and external relationships.<li><strong>Daily Operations</strong> - How the organization manages its daily work.<li><strong>People Philosophy</strong> - How the organization develops its people.</ul><p>Each of the main areas has a series of scales which explore different aspects of how the organization operates. Since some aspects of a company’s culture are more important to you than others, we suggest you think about the five or six aspects of a company’s culture that are most important to you. Are there a few aspects that are "must haves"?  Are there any aspects that are potential "deal breakers"? What is it about the "must haves" that energize and motivate you? What is it about the "deal breakers" that demotivate you?<p>Finally, think about what could be done to put more of what you like into a job as well as how the position might be modified to lessen the aspects you might not like. These thoughts could be the basis for an exploratory discussion during the hiring process. Included in your report below, in the right-hand column, are some questions to consider while preparing for these career discussions.<p>Thank you for taking Strategia Analytics Diagnostics™ <strong>Candidate Cultural Alignment Profile™</strong>.<p>With Appreciation,<p><span>The Strategia Analytics Team</span><p><br><br><h3>Main Area 